Sometimes in vs code you may not be able to give variable value to array like ;
int n;
a[n] // give you error in order to solve this issue follow this step 
To select g++ compiler 
step 1 : go to MinGw -> bin -> g++ -> press shift+right mouse button -> copy path
step 2 : open visual studio -> go to view -> Command pallete -> search for C++ (UI)
-> go to compiler path -> paste the g++ path and then scroll down and select IntelliSense mode ->
g++x64 
All done !! Happy Coding 
